HB59 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2
3
4 Relating to the Alabama State Board of Public
5 Accountancy; to amend Sections 34-1-2, 34-1-3, 34-1-4, 34-1-6,
6 34-1-7, 34-1-11, 34-1-14, and 34-1-16, Code of Alabama 1975;
7 to authorize the board to provide certain required
8 notifications by electronic mail; to authorize the board to
9 provide educational prerequisites to certain actions by rule;
10 to remove certain subjects required to be covered by the CPA
11 examination; to further provide for nonlicensed owners of CPA
12 firms; to further provide for the eligibility of individuals
13 to be permitted to practice public accountancy; to provide
14 that a firm cannot advertise that the firm is a CPA firm
15 unless it is registered as a CPA firm; and to make
16 nonsubstantive, technical revisions to update the existing
17 code language to current style.
18 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
19 Section 1. This act shall be known and may be cited as
20 the Pathways to CPA Act.
21 Section 2. Sections 34-1-2, 34-1-3, 34-1-4, 34-1-6,
22 34-1-7, 34-1-11, 34-1-14, and 34-1-16, Code of Alabama 1975,
23 are amended to read as follows:
