563 status penalty in an amount set by the board which is
564 graduated for the time of the inactivity.
565 (e) The experience requirement shall be one year of
566 experience in the practice of public accounting as defined by
567 the board's rules and regulations."
568 "§34-1-14
569 (a) Commencement of proceeding. The board may initiate
570 proceedings under this chapter either on its own motion or on
571 the complaint of any person.
572 (b) Notice; service and contents. A written notice
573 stating the nature of the charge or charges against the
574 accused and the time and place of the hearing before the board
575 on suchthe charges shall be served on the accused not less
576 than 30 days prior to the date of saidthe hearing either
577 personally or by mailing a copy thereof by registered or
578 certified mail to the address of the accused last known to the
579 board or by electronic mail to the last electronic mail
580 address of the accused known to the board with electronic mail
581 delivery receipt requested.
582 (c) Failure to appear. If, after having been served
583 with thea notice of hearing as provided for herein, the
584 accused fails to appear at saidthe hearing and defend, the
585 board may proceed to hear evidence against him or her and may
586 enter suchan order as shallmay be justified by the evidence,
587 which. The order shall be final unless he or shethe accused
588 petitions for a review thereof as provided hereinof the order;
