589 provided, that withinnot more than 30 days from the date of
590 any order, upon a showing of good cause for failing to appear
591 and defend, the board may reopen the proceedings and may
592 permit the accused to submit evidence in his or her behalf.
593 (d) Counsel; witnesses; cross-examination. At any
594 hearing, the accused may appear in person or by counsel,
595 produce evidence and witnesses on his or her own behalf,
596 cross-examine witnesses, and examine such evidence as may be
597 produced against him or her. A professional association or
598 corporation may be represented before the board by counsel or
599 by a shareholder who is a certified public accountant or
600 public accountant of this state in good standing. The accused
601 shall be entitled, on application to the board, to the
602 issuance of subpoenas to compel the attendance of witnesses on
603 his or her behalf.
604 (e) Subpoenas; testimony; deposition.
